reviews.text:
I'm not exactly sure how to rate this place. It looks like a dive bar with sticky floors and mismatched furniture, but has a rather upscale menu and is definitely pricier than expected.

They have a great variety of drinks and our cheese board and soup were delicious. The burger was just ok, but the service was great and both our waiter and the hostess were very friendly and welcoming.

Attended a dinner here for a graduation of a friend from VA Tech. A reservation was made for 14 people. We arrived and were greeted by the host.

The host verified the table was ready and then we were shown to the table. I had no idea how big this place is! You walk in and there is a bar area, but the restaurant is huge and has a lot of tables.

Our waiter was prompt and and got the beverages going and appetizers ordered. When the restaurant of the party showed up orders were taken. I ordered the risotto with shrimp.

The wait for the food was less than 30 minutes which was pretty good for a party of 14! The waiter was excellent with refills for drinks.

My risotto unfortunately did not come with the shrimp as ordered. I also found the dish way too sweet. It was more like a dessert. I was offered a free dessert l, but they ran out of the cake.

With good service like that I would definitely go back and try the place again. Orders can get mixed up and the customer service shows this place cares about the dining experience.

We stopped by 622 North and were seriously impressed. The daily special of pork dumplings was amazing. So flavorful and perfectly cooked. I got the steak salad and it was much better than I expected. The steak had great flavor and was cooked just right. We also tried the duck breast which was delicious and very well seasoned. Everything we ordered was fresh and full of flavor. The quality of the food here really stood out.

Whoever cooked my risotto has definitely never ate it to know the right amount of ingredients and when too much is too much. It was very greasy and heavy on the pepper. However, The poached eggs were poached perfectly (I ordered an extra egg, usually it‚Äôs only one). I couldn‚Äôt eat it with amount of pepper that it was cooked with.
Great place for dinner in Blacksburg. Prices are reasonable. Menu is solid. Staff is excellent shout out to Monica thanks for the outstanding service.

editorial_summary.overview: Eclectic bistro fare served in a Victorian house with understated decor, a wine bar & pool tables.

detailedReviews.text: First time at this restaurant - it was not busy - I'll come back to see if anything changes BUT if you like SALT and no actual ingredient flavor this place is for you.  Five stars if you have the pallet of an alligator.  I'm not sure if most people who gave this 5 stars have actually cooked their own food (poorly) or they lost their sense of taste due to COVID - but holly salt lick Bat Man!!!!!  Now I will say this, it could have been my order only BUT literally 99% of our group spit out the food and did not eat any more (with the exception of 1 person - who let's face it has not real taste due to COVID - so high salt content would benefit them).  I will say (and the reason it received 2 stars) was due to the service.  The service was amazing - very attentive and made sure we had everything we needed - but the food - how do I put a GAG emoji into this post???  Fire the cook (because no Chef would let this dog food come out of the kitchen) and hire someone who actually understands that salt is not a primary food group.

We went for lunch before VT graduation. They were able to accommodate a bigger group and the food was great!! Service was excellent too. We will definitely come back when we visit Blacksburg !

detailedReviews.author: Julie Boyer
detailedReviews.text: I‚Äôm a local and eat here regularly; 622 is consistently the best restaurant in the area. Great specials, wonderful soups, and excellent service are the norm here. Brunch is fabulous. I do not know how the kitchen consistently gets the food out so wonderfully prepared so efficiently. Their sommelier, Ray, is always happy to pair the perfect wine with your dinner selection. Great drink and beer selections, too.

detailedReviews.author: Theresa Barnhart- Radachowsky
detailedReviews.text: Amazing food. Service was professional.

detailedReviews.author: Maria Favro
detailedReviews.text: This place was so cute! Very cozy and homey vibes. There was a more casual area with a bar and then a more formal sit down area as well. Grant was our server. He was so kind and knowledgable about the menu. My boyfriend and I are both in the restaurant industry so we can definitely vouch for how great our experience was. You guys are killing it!!! Thank you!!

detailedReviews.text:
We went there yesterday for dinner. I ordered the chicken tacos and French fries. The fries was so salty! I couldn't do it. The grit is not grit rather polenta lol üòÇ I can't.
Ridiculous!

detailedReviews.author: Noah W.
detailedReviews.text: Great food, cool spot. Not cheap.

detailedReviews.author: Beth Graves
detailedReviews.text: We were in town for the weekend and came in as a party of five. Our server Alex was outstanding. He knew the menu, made great suggestions, and provided excellent service. I had the white fish special and it was delicious!

detailedReviews.author: Zeta Mu Phi Executive Director
detailedReviews.text: We chose this location for a business brunch. The gave us a private, back room with exceptional service and even better food. You can't go wrong with this place!

detailedReviews.author: Abigail Stiglich
detailedReviews.text: I've been here for breakfast, lunch, and dinner multiple times, and I highly recommend it for breakfast! I recently visited for my college graduation dinner and wasn't wowed. I ordered a burger and fries, and the portions were small for a $17 burger. 622 North offers unique styles and flavors compared to other restaurants in the area. Overall, the food was good, the drinks were strong, and the service was great, but there are other restaurants in the area that offer equal or better options.

detailedReviews.author: Bonnie Kirby
detailedReviews.text: My favorite place in Blacksburg! Love the food.

detailedReviews.author: Deb Frankovich
detailedReviews.text: We reserved lunch for 10 on Saturday May 10th during VT's very busy graduation week.  622 North did not disappoint, the service was excellent and the food was even better. We did not feel rushed, it was a perfect way to enjoy a family lunch with great quality food and a pleasant atmosphere. The bar top tables were dressed up with white table cloths to add a special touch to our event. We will definitely come back next time we are in Blacksburg.

detailedReviews.author: Laura Thomas
detailedReviews.text: My husband and I love 622! We usually have dinner here for our anniversary. I have recommended 622 North to a lot of family and friends! I‚Äôve never been disappointed with any dish I‚Äôve ordered. Definitely make a reservation ahead of time!

detailedReviews.author: Jimmy Russell
detailedReviews.text: This may have been one of the most disappointing experiences I have ever had. After seeing the online presence and reviews, in addition to looking at the menu online, all seemed to be set up for us to have an enjoyable experience and maybe even find a new go to when in Blacksburg. When we walked in I knew right away we had made a mistake and we almost turned around, I wish we had. I could have looked over the majority of what I saw as red flags but the most disappointing part was the fact that the place just opened up at 5 for dinner and we were one of the first to sit down. There is no way that the Brussels sprouts and mash potatoes had been made in the last hour much less 4 hours. The meatloaf was a 5 out of 10 at best but the rest of the plate was not even close to something I could manage to eat without gagging (cold, dry and just old in general). I could go on but will leave it at that.

detailedReviews.author: Alex Zhang
detailedReviews.text: Solid brunch spot

detailedReviews.author: Jon Probst
detailedReviews.text:
Went to Easter brunch with wife. She had requested a closer table due to less walking for disabled person with cane. Which hostess replied after seating in furthest section of the restaurant with "I'm sorry" with no further assistance.
I'd ordered French Toast with bacon and it wasn't even cooked thru. Still wet and runny. Id requested another, to which still came back same way minus, bacon.
Wife's breakfast potatoes were like croutons instead of soft, hard..
For the prices of entrees and restaurant with reservations, you figure that the chef would know how to cook items served.
Bad experience. Will not return..

detailedReviews.author: Trevor West
detailedReviews.text: Amazing restaurant! I had my first date with my girlfriend here, and it was a really good choice. The food is exceptional, and the service is awesome! I highly recommend the filet mignon, but I also recommend the special I had my last visit (hot Italian sandwich with beef) if it's available.

detailedReviews.author: Jake Howes
detailedReviews.text: We had a leisurely Sunday lunch. It was great food with great service. We will definitely be back.

detailedReviews.author: Billy Tu
detailedReviews.text:
Fairly good experience here! Came on a Saturday for lunch, and it was very quiet. Service was friendly and prompt. As for the food, it was good too! I went with the Turkey BLT which I had no complaints about. I can't really attest to how the place is at dinner, but I imagine that it could get quite busy. Didn't order any alcohol, so I don't really have much to add there.

Solid spot, and I'd come back to try the dinner.

detailedReviews.author: Mukesh Bhakta
detailedReviews.text: Ordered four different cocktails and were excellent including the Milagros Reposado tea infused tequila cocktail(excellent and not overly sweet). The Brussels sprouts are crispy and amazing and artichoke dip is great. The mushroom sandwiches are crispy and good flavor. The main entree with potatoes rounds little oily though. Took my daughter and her room mates out and they all enjoyed it.

detailedReviews.author: Julie
detailedReviews.text: It's always a treat to go here for dinner, or any meal for that matter. The food never disappoints, and the drinks are superb. Ray is always fantastic!

detailedReviews.author: DM B (Dave)
detailedReviews.text: A fine dining experience with reasonable prices and great service

detailedReviews.author: po
detailedReviews.text: great atmosphere and great vibes with a large wine selection with a nice menu to go with it. can hold big celebrations along with smaller dates if necessary. great service and everyone was super kind. will come back for more items on the menu

Brussels sprouts and artichoke dip were delicious as well. Our server was very nice. Excellent house dressings for the salad!

detailedReviews.author: D J
detailedReviews.text: Went for a business meal and had a great experience. Food was amazing - duck, meatloaf, cheese board, ravioli, burger. All our choices were flavorful and very filling. Good wine menu. The service was fine. I loved the layout of the restaurant. We will definitely return.

detailedReviews.author: Eric de Sturler
detailedReviews.text: Good steak dinner,  good beer and wine selection.

detailedReviews.author: Dean C
detailedReviews.text: The atmosphere is a little week. The food is worth a visit and the service is excellent.

detailedReviews.author: Ron Snyder
detailedReviews.text: Honey mustard dressing was spicy.  BBQ sauce tasted like vinegar.  Server was not attentive.

detailedReviews.author: Greg Green
detailedReviews.text: Food and service were really great people very friendly.

detailedReviews.author: Amy Hall
detailedReviews.text: Amy Gray (Hall) lived here after birth to age 6 in Frank Gray & Bessie V. Cook Gray. Home to left was Elliot D. Chestnut & Mary V. Gray & 3 children. I Have my Price ancestry to 1735. Also, Cheese Does not belong on green tomatoes Ever. Not in Atlanta  but Fruit salsa is Fine.

detailedReviews.author: Jennifer Sutherland
detailedReviews.text: Always Terrific food! This is a go-to when in town visiting our son at VT. The charcuterie as a shared app is delicious. Highly recommend the pork chop with cherry sauce, creamy risotto and Brussel sprouts. Different atmosphere depending on where you sit. Bar is very laid back, and main dining rooms are much nicer. Food is still great no matter where you sit.

detailedReviews.author: Brandi Smith
detailedReviews.text: Neat atmosphere and great service. 622 salad and the spicy chicken sandwich were great.

detailedReviews.author: Wendy Baldwin

detailedReviews.author: Indiana Mork

detailedReviews.author: Aaron Sweeney
detailedReviews.text: Menu was great, food was well plated and tasted amazing, drinks were good as well. Server was great! Unfortunately portions of my chicken were severely undercooked. If that weren‚Äôt the case, an easy 5 stars.

detailedReviews.author: Jeff Bowman
detailedReviews.text: The food was great. The service was friendly and pleasant.

detailedReviews.author: Grace Monger
detailedReviews.text: Incredible restaurant, consistently excellent experience, great cocktails, fast and friendly service. Food is always good and good portions

detailedReviews.author: Randy Kates
detailedReviews.text:
This is really a terrific restaurant - friendly overall vibe, great service oriented staff and novel layout in transformed historic Blacksburg Mansion.
We were fortunate to have the amazing Alex as our waiter - who walked us thru the broad menu and highlighted specials - and handled several special preparation requests with ease.
For us this is an overlooked gem in the ‚ÄòBurg, and if you‚Äôre looking for a special night out, or some fun with friends and family, this should be on your list to visit next night out in Blacksburg. (And if you‚Äôre just looking for a refreshing adult beverage or craft beer - Franks Bar inside is ready to quench your thirst) üòéüèÜü¶É

detailedReviews.author: Liz De La Rosa
detailedReviews.text: I feel bad writing this because the service was great and because there was a Frank Sinatra picture. The coke I got smelled like metal and I could not drink it. I feel like the atmosphere of the place is dive bar trying to serve fancy dishes which was my mistake of trying to order a risotto. The risotto was flavorless and the steak as well. I am not picky I‚Äôve been told so my husband was surprised when I didn‚Äôt eat it. The only thing I could eat was the asparagus. (Husband ate steak, but said it was ok). Paid $29 for a dish that was not worth it. Will not return.

detailedReviews.author: Genesis Peterson
detailedReviews.text: I wish I could say how the food was. I sat at the bar for 13 plus minutes(I counted) waiting for my order to be taken and I was passed over by two patrons by the bartenders. There was 1 other person at the bar when I walked in. I was excited about the duck and half of wine. This happened 7/19.

detailedReviews.author: Shareka W
detailedReviews.text:
The food was delicious and our servers were very friendly and helpful with drink and food suggestions. They have alot of great cocktails and beer and the apps are delicious! Just a warning but you cannot get entrees until later in the evening on weekends. I went around 2pm on a Sunday and were told this. It wasn't a big deal for me because I tried so many of the apps I wasn't every hungry afterwards.

I couldn't see the entire restaurant but from where I sat all tables were high top tables. The ones along the wall had a booth seat along the wall and counter height chairs on the other sides. I saw one table with booth seating.

detailedReviews.author: Erin Cox
detailedReviews.text: This place is amazing! Very creative and flavorful dishes with a varied selection. I normally hate fish, but I got a fish dish here and absolutely loved it!
